The paper discusses privacy mechanisms for estimating the distribution of personal data, which is a topic related to data privacy and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes personalized mechanisms with semantic tags, which suggests a focus on database management (cs.DB). The paper discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes mechanisms for estimating distributions, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
